{"questionId":"27638","questionHtml":"<p>Determine the maximum possible value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, justifying your answer.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A is a subset of B&nbsp; (so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mi>A</mi></mfenced></math>).&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> This may be conveyed in a clearly labelled diagram where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> is completely inside <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>, or in a written explanation indicating that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mi>A</mi></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><br>so the maximum value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>R0A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27638","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.6c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Determine the maximum possible value of P(A∩B), justifying your answer.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and proba